    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12568#issuecomment-4660671516\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12568\">issue #12568</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>@badeend if you don't mind me pinging you again on this, I was wondering if you had thoughts on this issue/test? On Linux at least this is returning <code>Ok(())</code> instead of an error. On macOS I get <code>ErrorCode::RemoteUnreachable</code> as Saul mentions.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 601443985,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1781014492
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>badeend <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12568#issuecomment-4697932934\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12568\">issue #12568</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Hmm, never got a notification for that first ping. Anyhow..</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Yes, good catch @saulecabrera.  I think this got lost somewhere during the p2-&gt;p3 conversion. The P2 implementation _does_ have this check:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/ff944c96c9bee03da951e75e21aba26f3ee99ebd/crates/wasi/src/p2/host/udp.rs#L319-L322\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/ff944c96c9bee03da951e75e21aba26f3ee99ebd/crates/wasi/src/p2/host/udp.rs#L319-L322</a></p>\n<p>I've opened a PR to do the same thing in P3: <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13631\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13631</a></p>\n</blockquote>",
